Summary for Archit

What Thanus's node does:
It's the last step in the pipeline. Once Marcus's AWS code gets the face recognition result back from Shashank, it calls one function: handle_recognition_result("granted") or handle_recognition_result("denied"). That's the only integration point.
From that single call, the node automatically handles everything physical:

RGB LED on the PYNQ changes colour (green = granted, red = denied, cyan = processing)
Servo rotates to open the door for 3 seconds on granted, stays shut on denied
Buzzer plays a distinct audio pattern for each state so you can hear the result without looking
Security escalation — if 3 denials happen in a row, or 5 within 2 minutes, an alarm fires automatically (rapid red flash + alarm buzzer pattern)
Logging — every event is timestamped and written to attendance_log.txt
Night mode — between 8pm and 8am, if a frame image is passed in alongside a denial, the face capture is saved automatically

The physical buttons on the PYNQ board also work standalone: BTN0 simulates granted, BTN1 simulates denied, BTN3 shuts the system down cleanly.
Archit doesn't need to touch any of this code. His pipeline feeds into Shashank → Marcus → this node. The only thing that matters to this node is the single function call Marcus makes at the end.
